article.headline: Georgia Southern 59, Elon 44
article.story: STATESBORO, Ga. (AP) -- Louis Graham scored 25 points and grabbed 11 rebounds and Matthew Fields also had a double-double to lead Georgia Southern to a 59-44 win over Elon on Saturday night. The Eagles (19-8, 12-5 Southern Conference) went on a 10-0 run late in the first half, building a 26-13 lead. Six points were scored off free throws, while Fields made a layup and Anthony Marshall finished the run with a jumper. Fields scored 14 points and grabbed 12 rebounds and Marshall added 12 for the Eagles. Georgia Southern pushed its lead to 50-31 -- its largest of the game -- with 7:41 left in the second half on a jumper by Julian Allen. The Phoenix (10-16, 8-10) would pull no closer than 12 points. Montell Watson led Elon with 14 points.
